### **4. `.gitignore`**

This file ensures that unnecessary files are not committed to Git (e.g., Python bytecode files, virtual environments).

```gitignore
# Python bytecode files
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]

# Virtual environment
venv/
env/

# IDE settings (optional)
.idea/
.vscode/

# Distribution/Packaging
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/
